  "texts": [
    "The quality of each SSL method primarily depends on the quality of the pretext tasks.",
    "The pretext task must capture useful information to ensure the learned representations are meaningful.",
    "The purpose of our work is to thus adapt and compare recent state-of-the-art SSL techniques derived from computer vision (i.e., MAE and data2vec) to HAR and establish a relevant evaluation framework.",
    "This adaptation proved to be far from trivial and necessitated substantial technical and conceptual efforts.",
    "In particular, since SSL techniques are usually closely tied to the network's architecture, we conducted the implementation with two widely employed architectures: CNNs and Transformers."
  ],
